      <title>How to Get Into Interior Decorating</title>
      <link>http://www.fourpoundbrain.com/how-to-get-into-interior-decorating/</link>
      <comments>http://www.fourpoundbrain.com/how-to-get-into-interior-decorating/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sun, 24 Aug 2008 15:01:57 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Jennifer</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Home & Garden]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[How To]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[interior decorating]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[interior design]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.fourpoundbrain.com/?p=141</guid>
      <description>So, you think you might have an eye for interior design, but are wondering how you can benefit from this skill and talent. Wondering how to get into interior decorating? Read the steps below to find out how you can put your ideas to good use, and even help others. Step 1: Don&amp;#8217;t be afraid [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/four-pound-brain/Four_Pound_Brain-How_to_Get_Into_Interior_Decorating.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>So, you think you might have an eye for interior design, but are wondering how you can benefit from this skill and talent. <em>Wondering how to get into interior decorating?</em> Read the steps below to find out how you can put your ideas to good use, and even help others.</p>
<p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Don&#8217;t be afraid to sit around with others with the same goals and talk about what you can do. Bringing together more people to brainstorm is always beneficial, especially when talking optimistically about the future.</p>
<p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Interior decorating involves a career including creative skills that allow homes and business to have a more beautiful and comfortable feel, making it appealing to those who occupy the space. This is a job that would be have to be satisfying at the end of the day.  If the desire is there, becoming an interior decorator is possible. There is no special education or experience needed to enter this field, unless you want to be a certified decorator.</p>
<p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Work on training your eye, which already is sharp when it comes to design. When you look at a room, you know what looks good and see what should be changed. You can train your eye by studying what other people think are good designs. You also can educate yourself by taking courses, reading books, visiting Web sites or even talking with retailers of products used in decorating, i.e. paint, carpet, lighting, etc.</p>
<p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Use your personal space to practice. As Dorothy said, &#8220;There&#8217;s no place like home.&#8221; You can start by rearranging furniture or painting your walls a different color. You can also volunteer your services to others who might be in need of interior decorating.</p>
<p><strong>Step 5:</strong> Make sure to keep samples of all of your work in a portfolio, including any documents that would show a person benefits of hiring you.</p>
<p><strong>Step 6:</strong> Now that you have established that you would like a career in interior design, you must decide whether you want to work for someone else or start your own business in the field. Get your name out there by networking with other professionals in the field and be sure to showcase your work.</p>
<p><em>Tips</em></p>
<ul>
<li>When first starting out, be reasonable with your pricing to get more business. Aim lower because your initial goal is to get more clients. Word-of-mouth is always the best advertising method. Once you have a firm clientele base, you can raise your prices a bit because people will associate your name with quality work, as long as the job is being done right.</li>
</ul>
]]></content:encoded>
