      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>You have the Linux program Bind9, and you want to know how to set up a DNS server name using that program. It&#8217;s not as complicated as it sounds.  Follow the steps below to figure out how to do it, and have fun with your configuring.</p>
<p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Server names like ns1.nixcraft.net can be used as a vanity DNS for theos.in domain. There are three things to be aware of:  your real DNS server, the Vanity DNS and the IP address for both the real and vanity servers.</p>
<p><strong>Step 2:</strong> For example, your real DNS server is ns1.nixcraft.net and your vanity DNS is ns1.theos.in.  Your IP address for both is 202.54.1.20.</p>
<p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Another example is DNS server ns2.nixcraft.net with a vanity DNS ns2.theos.in and the above listed IP address.  It just takes a little tweaking, but it can be done with ease.</p>
<p><em>Tips</em></p>
<ul>
<li>Instead of using ns1.nixcraft.net, you will use ns1.theos.in for the theos.in.  Remember to replace the domain name and IPs according to your program.</li>
</ul>
<p><em>Items Needed</em></p>
